										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2666" src="/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/sleeper.gif" alt="" width="686" height="323" /></p>
<p>AHHH why is it so difficult to export rigged model to Three.js?</p>
<p>This is a reminder post of how did I export with correct joint rotations.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>[From Maya] &#8211; export selection as FBX, set Up Axis from Y to Z</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone  wp-image-2667" src="/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.18.58-PM.png" alt="" width="563" height="148" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.18.58-PM.png 700w, /wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.18.58-PM-300x79.png 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.18.58-PM-400x105.png 400w, /wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.18.58-PM-210x55.png 210w" sizes="(max-width: 563px) 100vw, 563px" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>[Import to Blender] &#8211; Scale up!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>[Export to Three.js] &#8211; Select Mesh and export as Three.js. Geometry: also select &#8220;Bones&#8221; and &#8220;Skinning&#8221;. Type: choose &#8220;Geometry&#8221; instead of BufferGeometry. Skeletal animations: select &#8220;Rest&#8221; instead of &#8220;Pose&#8221;</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone  wp-image-2668" src="/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.17.46-PM.png" alt="" width="294" height="364" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.17.46-PM.png 426w, /wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.17.46-PM-242x300.png 242w, /wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.17.46-PM-400x496.png 400w, /wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.17.46-PM-210x260.png 210w" sizes="(max-width: 294px) 100vw, 294px" /> <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone  wp-image-2669" src="/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.18.07-PM.png" alt="" width="257" height="364" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.18.07-PM.png 436w, /wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.18.07-PM-212x300.png 212w, /wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.18.07-PM-400x567.png 400w, /wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-27-at-6.18.07-PM-210x298.png 210w" sizes="(max-width: 257px) 100vw, 257px" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>[Import to Three.js] &#8211; Load with THREE.JSONLoader. Set &#8220;skinning: true&#8221; in material. Create with THREE.SkinnedMesh. And finally manipulate with THREE.SkinnedMesh&#8217;s skeleton.bones array.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Geez.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
